              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Instant Reconnection</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Switches between WiFi and cellular in ~1ms. Perfect for mobile users. OpenVPN takes seconds to minutes to reconnect.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Battery Efficient</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Uses significantly less CPU than OpenVPN, preserving phone battery. Ideal for always-on VPN connections.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Auditable Security</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Tiny codebase makes security audits easier. Uses modern cryptography (Curve25519, ChaCha20) instead of aging algorithms. Formally verified for correctness.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Open Source & Free</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Dual-licensed (GPLv2 and BSD). No patents or licensing fees. Built into the Linux kernel.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Disadvantages</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
