      <section id="openvpn" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. OpenVPN: The Veteran</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          OpenVPN has been the industry standard since 2001. It's not the fastest, but it's the most battle-tested, configurable, and widely supported protocol. If you need reliability over speed, OpenVPN is still king.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Technical Specs</h3>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> AES-256-GCM (or ChaCha20 with newer builds)</li>
            <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> SHA-256 or SHA-512 HMAC</li>
            <li><strong>Key Exchange:</strong> RSA-2048 or higher</li>
            <li><strong>Transport:</strong> TCP (reliable) or UDP (faster)</li>
            <li><strong>Ports:</strong> Configurable (commonly 1194, 443, 80)</li>
            <li><strong>Code Size:</strong> 400,000+ lines of C code</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Advantages</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Highly Configurable</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Supports TCP and UDP, custom ports, proxy configurations, and advanced routing. Can bypass almost any firewall or network restriction.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Battle-Tested Security</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                20+ years in production. Audited countless times. No critical vulnerabilities when configured properly. Trusted by governments and enterprises.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Works Everywhere</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Supported on every platform: Windows, macOS, Linux, iOS, Android, routers, even Raspberry Pi. Compatible with older systems.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Obfuscation Support</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Can disguise VPN traffic as HTTPS (port 443) to bypass censorship. Works in China, Russia, and other restrictive countries when WireGuard is blocked.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Open Source</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                GPLv2 license. Transparent and community-audited. No hidden backdoors or proprietary code.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Disadvantages</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Slower Than WireGuard</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Typically 20-40% speed reduction vs. 5-15% for WireGuard. The large codebase and TLS overhead slow things down.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Slow Reconnection</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Takes 5-30 seconds to reconnect after network changes. Poor for mobile users switching between WiFi and cellular.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Battery Drain</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                CPU-intensive encryption drains phone batteries faster than WireGuard. Not ideal for always-on VPN on mobile.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Complex Configuration</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Setting up OpenVPN manually is harder than WireGuard. More settings = more ways to misconfigure and create security holes.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

