      <section id="ikev2" class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. IKEv2/IPSec: The Mobile Champion</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          IKEv2 (Internet Key Exchange version 2) paired with IPSec is a solid protocol developed by Microsoft and Cisco. It's faster than OpenVPN, more stable than L2TP, and excels at reconnecting on mobile devices.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Technical Specs</h3>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> AES-256 (via IPSec)</li>
            <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> PSK (Pre-Shared Key) or digital certificates</li>
            <li><strong>Key Exchange:</strong> Diffie-Hellman (Groups 14, 15, 16, etc.)</li>
            <li><strong>Transport:</strong> UDP port 500, 4500</li>
            <li><strong>Platform Support:</strong> Native on Windows, macOS, iOS; third-party apps on Android/Linux</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Advantages</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Fast Reconnection (MOBIKE)</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                IKEv2 supports MOBIKE (Mobility and Multihoming), which allows instant reconnection when switching networks. Perfect for iPhones switching between WiFi and cellular.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Native Support on Apple Devices</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Built into iOS and macOS‚Äîno third-party apps needed. Easy to configure via Settings.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Faster Than OpenVPN</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Outperforms OpenVPN in speed tests. Uses efficient algorithms and less overhead.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-green-600 text-xl">‚úì</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Stable Connections</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Less prone to random disconnections than OpenVPN. Uses UDP efficiently without TCP's retry delays.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Disadvantages</h3>
        <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Limited Port Options</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Uses UDP 500/4500, which can be blocked by firewalls. Can't disguise as HTTPS like OpenVPN.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Developed by Microsoft/Cisco</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Some privacy advocates distrust closed-source contributions from corporations with government ties. However, the protocol itself is open and auditable.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-600 text-xl">‚úó</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Slower Than WireGuard</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">
                Still uses older cryptography and has more overhead than WireGuard.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-600 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">When to Use IKEv2</h3>
          <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
            <li>‚Ä¢ You're on iPhone/iPad and want native VPN support (no app needed)</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You frequently switch between WiFi and cellular and need instant reconnection</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ Your VPN provider doesn't support WireGuard</li>
            <li>‚Ä¢ You need better battery life than OpenVPN but more maturity than WireGuard</li>
          </ul>
